	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />This pretty much reminds me Fire Emblem, exept that you don't get a false ending, but just a death quote on the death of a character. You still have only one life, no continues, etc... (exept that you can sometimes continue the game if you wish even if not all characters are alive).
<br />
<br />Live a Live (SNES) also had a lot of False endings, each featuring "false credits".

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


